### A1. Create a payment (CRUD POST) — expect CREATED event in Mongo
# Expected: 201, then payment_audit_trail has a doc with action=CREATED
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/payments
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rideId": 1,
  "userId": 1,
  "amount": 250.00,
  "method": "CREDIT_CARD",
  "status": "COMPLETED"
}

### A2. Process refund on a COMPLETED payment — expect REFUNDED event
# First ensure a COMPLETED payment exists (update one via CRUD if needed)
# Expected: 200, payment_audit_trail has action=REFUNDED for this paymentId
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/payments/3/refund
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "driver no show"
}


### 2a. Create a PERCENTAGE coupon (50% off, max 10 uses)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/coupons
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "TEST50",
  "discountType": "PERCENTAGE",
  "discountValue": 50.0,
  "maxUses": 10,
  "currentUses": 0,
  "expiryDate": "2027-12-31T23:59:59",
  "active": true
}

### Paste returned coupon id below:
@couponId = <paste_coupon_id_here>

### 2b. Create a FIXED coupon (20 off, max 5 uses)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/coupons
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "FIXED20",
  "discountType": "FIXED",
  "discountValue": 20.0,
  "maxUses": 5,
  "currentUses": 0,
  "expiryDate": "2027-12-31T23:59:59",
  "active": true
}


### A3. Apply coupon to a PENDING payment — expect COUPON_APPLIED event
# Expected: 200, payment_audit_trail has action=COUPON_APPLIED
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/payments/1/coupons/1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### A4. Retry a FAILED payment — expect RETRY_ATTEMPTED event
# First set a payment to FAILED status via CRUD update
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/payments/2
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "FAILED"
}

### Then retry it — expect RETRY_ATTEMPTED + status becomes COMPLETED
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/payments/3/retry
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

